Abdomen: Ventrites 1–5 subquadrate, rugulose, conspicuously, finely punctate; clothed with short, pale, recumbent setae. Ventrites 1-4 with a feebly elevated, longitudinal, pale carina which does not attain posterolateral angles and a pair of large, pale, shallow impressions near sides (
Fig. 27
). Fifth ventrite feebly convex; subtriangular in shape; surface rugose, shallowly, finely punctate; lateral margins oblique, somewhat arcuate; posterior margin shallowly and broadly emarginate (
Fig. 6
). Sixth ventrite subtriangular in shape; reduced; broader than long; lateral margins oblique, somewhat arcuate; hind margin conspicuously reduced, shallowly, U-shaped emarginate; surface feebly convex, shiny, finely punctate (
Fig. 6
). Fifth tergite rugulose; lateral margins moderately oblique; posterior margin truncate. Sixth tergite reduced, subquadrate, broader than long; lateral margins oblique, feebly arcuate; posterior margin truncate, extending slightly beyond apical margin of sixth ventrite.
